[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Universal gadget chain pattern:**                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Look for classes with dangerous method calls in `initialize`,                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `marshal_load`, or implicit method calls.                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Exploitation Strategy                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **1. Identify deserialization point:**                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Cookie values (session data)                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Hidden form fields (ViewState)                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - API parameters                                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - File uploads                                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Message queues                                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **2. Determine technology stack:**                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Error messages                                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - HTTP headers (X-Powered-By)                                                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - File extensions                                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Framework signatures                                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **3. Identify available gadgets:**                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Check application dependencies                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Look for common vulnerable libraries                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test known gadget chains                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **4. Generate and deliver payload:**                                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Identify format → Select gadget chain → Generate payload → Encode if needed  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m → Inject                                                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### PHAR Deserialization (PHP)                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m PHP deserializes PHAR metadata automatically when accessed via `phar://`:    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```php                                                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m // Create malicious PHAR                                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $phar = new Phar('evil.phar');                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $phar->startBuffering();                                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $phar->addFromString('test.txt', 'test');                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $phar->setStub('<?php __HALT_COMPILER(); ?>');                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m // Inject serialized object as metadata                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $object = new VulnerableClass();                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $phar->setMetadata($object);                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m $phar->stopBuffering();                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Triggering functions:**                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `file_exists`, `is_file`, `file_get_contents`, `fopen`, `include`, etc. with [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `phar://` wrapper.                                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Building Blocks Approach                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m DESERIALIZATION BUILDING BLOCKS:                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 1. Identify: serialization format and language                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 2. Locate: deserialization entry point                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 3. Enumerate: available libraries/gadgets                                    [34m│[0m
